I have used Pocket for years, I'd even get yearly emails telling me I was in the top 1% of Pocket users. So it means a lot when I say that if the latest update is indicative of where the app is going, I might stop using it. Fewer and fewer articles open in article view, which is the key feature I use this app for. Scrollbars are gone. I can no longer long press a link to save it to Pocket. I dont think Mozilla understands this app and the changes since they've owned it really show that.

One of my most used apps Something broke in recent update 1. No longer remembers where I was in the article. This is especially annoying for long reads. 2. When finishing an article (I hit archive button) it stays on the article and doesn't go back to reading list. They both seem like new bugs

App was really good but the April 13 update removed the two features I used it for. App no longer saves your place in an article if you close the app and they removed the ability to page through an article as if it were a kindle.
Must have tool if you are working with different articles
current version doesn't allow saving links from articles you read

Liked this app until a recent change made it so you have to Save an article to switch to article view. It was already annoying enough that articles don't automatically load in that view as I use Pocket to avoid web view. Now that I have to tap twice every time I open an article in this app I wonder why I'm even still using it. Will have to check out other options and replace.
The quality of the app has gone quite downhill. It starts tge article at the beginning whenever I restart. It makes the app nearly impossible to use.

What happened to Article view? I have loved this app since way, way back in the day, when it was still called Read it Later. I have chronic headaches, and having the ability to just use the simple article view, with the black background, allowed me to read a lot more, without all the distractions and extra light. I saved everything to Pocket so I could read it that way. Now the article view option is just gone. If I wanted to read the articles on the web, I wouldn't need to use Pocket.

With the latest update the scroll indicator on right edge of the screen is gone, so you can't see where you are in the article. Also, when you long press on a link in article view, it no longer shows options, such as adding that link to Pocket.

2 stars and cancelling premium: 1. Pocket continues to insert "utm_source=pocket_mylist" to the URL when sharing from pocket. What is the point of this ‚Äì to let the source website know when someone clicks a link I've shared that it came from My Pocket List?! 2. I can no longer long press on a link in an article to save, copy link, view in browser. Now I have open a link in a custom tab, press the pocket button in the top right and then save ON THE LEFT of the bottom sheet ‚Äì extra steps for what?

They broke a core feature (long pressing on a link to save it)...!? Volume key page flipping is gone?? Mark as Read leaves you on the thing you just read??? there are trashy promos at the end of every article. and I still want them to bring back their friend sharing feature. Please do user testing before rolling out core UX changes
